main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified flying objects (UFOs) were reported in Nenana, Alaska in January 1952 by military personnel, residents, and radar operators.
interesting points: One sighting described a bright, circular object at an estimated altitude of 2,000 to 3,000 feet, making irregular movements and hovering at times before disappearing at a high rate of speed.
Another report mentioned a bright, circular object hovering approximately 500 feet above the ground, then shooting straight up at an extremely high rate of speed.
A radar station observed multiple unidentified targets traveling at high speeds, making erratic movements, and disappearing from view.

Two independent observers reported an unusually bright bluish-white light hovering in the sky, remaining stationary for some minutes before moving off at a very high rate of speed in a northeasterly direction.
A USAF Radar Observer reported sighting three bright lights in the sky over Nenana, Alaska, with the duration of the sighting being approximately 10 minutes.
sighted object: various unidentified flying objects, including bright circular objects and bright bluish-white lights
photographs: no, the report does not include photographs
